description:
The Dual Recovery Coordinator will assist community agencies in improving their capacity to provide quality service to individuals with both mental illness and substance use disorder. This is a pass-through position with Family Service League, and work is performed under the supervision of Suffolk County Division of Community Mental Hygiene.

**RESPONSIBILITIES:**

· Identify workforce training needs, and facilitate cross-agency and cross-discipline competency-based staff development;

· Coordinate and facilitate a cross-system workgroup for providers to collaboratively develop solutions to systemic challenges;

· Assess the need for other specialized services for dually diagnosed clients;

· Arrange and/ or provide trainings to county and community agencies and organizations regarding issues specific to individuals affected by co-occurring disorders;

· Research and promote Evidenced Based Practices as they apply to populations with co-occurring disorders;

· Develop a resource guide to support staff development programs;

· Craft and disseminate accessible guidance documents to support educational activities;

· Measure the outcomes of system and client changes;

· Provide trainings and presentations to agency providers.

**QUALIFICATIONS:**

1. Master’s Degree in Human Services and Credentialed Alcohol and Substance Abuse Counselor (CASAC) preferred; OR

2. Bachelor’s degree with demonstrated relevant training experience plus CASAC considered;

**Candidates must also demonstrate at least 2 years of professional administrative and/or direct service experience in the fields of mental health and/or substance use disorder.**

**SKILLS, ABILITIES, AND PERSONAL CHARACTERISTICS:**

· Knowledge of the unique local conditions impacting dually diagnosed individuals and available resources;

· Excellent verbal and written communication skills;

· Effective research and presentation skills;

· Ability to promote collaboration amongst individuals and organizations;

· Ability to establish and maintain cooperative working relationships across programs, providers, and agencies;

· Proficient computer skills including Microsoft Office Suite, related tools, and database management programs.

**Note: Work hours are generally 9am-5pm, Monday-Friday. The position requires some flexibility for trainings and may include occasional evenings.** 

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: From $62,000.00 per year

Benefits:

* Dental insurance
* Employee assistance program
* Flexible spending account
* Health insurance
* Life insurance
* Paid time off
* Retirement plan
* Vision insurance

Schedule:

* Monday to Friday

Work Location: In person
